 Jeffreys Bay - In a rather unusual incident Police in Jeffreys Bay arrested two men for stealing the same bicycle within ten minutes in two separate incidents in Jeffreys Bay on Monday. "On Monday, at around 1pm, police responded to a complaint of house breaking in progress in Kwagga Street, Jeffreys Bay," described police spokesperson, Sergeant Majola Nkohli. "At the scene, police were given a description of a suspect, who stole a bicycle from the garage. "Police spotted the suspect fitting the same description about three kilometres away from the scene." Sgt Nkohli said that it is further alleged that the suspect on seeing a police vehicle, dropped a bicycle on the ground, and fled on foot towards the nearest informal settlement. "Police cornered the suspect in between shacks and arrested him," he described. "As police returned to the spot, where the bicycle was dropped, it was missing. "The bicycle wheel prints led the police to the nearest shack, where a bicycle was found and another man was arrested for possession of stolen property." Sgt Nkohli said that the two men, aged 22 and 26 years, are due to appear in the Humansdorp Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday. They face charges of possession of suspected stolen property and housebreaking and theft respectively. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 